com.kinvey.persistence.mapping
Interface MappedEntity

public interface MappedEntity

MappedEntity makes it easy to persist your domain object to Kinvey. Simply implement this interface and supply the appropriate key-mappings in getMapping() to identify which attributes should be persisted to the cloud.

Usage

MappedEntity interface requires 'getMapping()' to marshall data back and forth from java to JSON fields. 
 public class MyEntity implements MappedEntity {
     private String uname;
     private String id;
  
     public List getMapping() {
         return Arrays.asList(new MappedField[] { new MappedField("uname", "name"), 
                                                 new MappedField ("id", "_id") });
     }
  
     // Getters and setters for all fields are required
     public String getUname() { return uname; }
     public void setUname(String n) { uname = n; }
     public String getId() { return id; }
     public void setId(String i) { id = i; }
  
 }
